HomeAboutFounding Partners
FOUNDING PARTNERS

MINDY CORPORON, CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER
Mindy Corporon is a Managing Member and Co-Founder of Boyer & Corporon Wealth Management, LLC and serves as Chief Executive Officer.
As CEO, Mindy’s focus is on continuously developing strategy and improving the firm's processes and suite of services. She also meets personally with clients, frequently acting as liaison with other professionals. As part of BCWM's comprehensive approach on behalf of its family and institutional clients, Mindy often coordinates meetings among the key individuals who comprise the client’s professional wealth management team.
Mindy also leads and represents the firm in its civic and philanthropic efforts in Kansas City and beyond.  Under Mindy’s leadership, the firm has been recognized for its many professional accomplishments as selected by the community and peers.
Mindy was honored as one of the Kansas City metro area’s 25 “Women Who Mean Business” in 2010. She was also one of only 12 local entrepreneurs chosen for the prestigious Helzberg Entrepreneurial Mentoring Program (HEMP) in 2011. Those chosen must meet a strict set of criteria and devote themselves to a three-year program.
Mindy was first trained as a Financial Advisor at PaineWebber (now UBS) in 1994, rising to become a Vice President of Investments. The December 2006 issue of On Wall Street named Mindy as one of the top Financial Advisors under the age of 40.
Mindy graduated with her Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of Oklahoma in 1990. Now a resident of Stilwell, Kansas, Mindy and her family are active supporters of Operation Breakthrough, a local charity helping children who are living in poverty develop to their fullest potential. Mindy has served on the boards of the Community Foundation of Johnson County and the Blue Valley Educational Foundation, and as a member of the 2012 Donald H. Chisholm Planned Giving Council for the Children’s Mercy Hospitals and Clinics.
Mindy’s greatest passion is to lead  the Faith Always Wins Foundation and the Reat Griffin Underwood Memorial Fund which were established to celebrate the memory of Mindy’s son Reat and her father, William L. Corporon, MD, who were tragically murdered in a hate crime in the Spring of 2014. Mindy continues to chair SevenDays: Make a Ripple, Change the World, a week-long event that brings communities together to celebrate diversity across races, religions and cultures.Download vCard


