Download vCardRICHARD BOYER, CHIEF INVESTMENT OFFICERRichard Boyer is a Managing Member and Founder of Boyer & Corporon Wealth Management, LLC and serves as Chief Investment Officer.
Richard has over 33 years of experience in the financial services industry, becoming a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ professional in 1988. In 2001, he earned the Chartered Financial Analyst® designation, joining the ranks of those few professionals worldwide who hold both designations. Richard is the charter member of BCWM’s Investment Committee.
All client portfolios are managed in-house at BCWM, and Richard, as our Chief Investment Officer, oversees all asset allocation and security selection. He also meets regularly with clients in order to check progress toward their financial goals.
Richard earned a Bachelor of Arts from the University of Kansas. Richard resides in Leawood, Kansas with his wife.


