Boyer & Corporon Wealth Management LLC Reduces Stake in Novartis AG (NVS)
Evrard Martin
Juillet 14, 2017



Part












Independent Advisor Alliance boosted its stake in shares of Novartis AG (NYSE:NVS) by 342.3% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the SEC. Novartis AG accounts for approximately 1.0% of Lcnb Corp's holdings, making the stock its 27th largest position. Independent Advisor Alliance's holdings in Novartis AG were worth $390,000 at the end of the most recent quarter.
Several other institutional investors have also bought and sold shares of the company. North Star Investment Management Corp. increased its position in Novartis AG by 50.3% in the first quarter. WFG Advisors LP now owns 4,182 shares of the company's stock worth $419,000 after buying an additional 2,663 shares in the last quarter. TCI Wealth Advisors Inc. increased its position in Novartis AG by 20.0% in the first quarter. Marco Investment Management LLC now owns 32,765 shares of the company's stock worth $2,433,000 after buying an additional 400 shares in the last quarter.Stock market analysts and brokers have recently amended their target prices on shares of Novartis AG (NYSE:NVS). The fund owned 5,286 shares of the company's stock after buying an additional 4,091 shares during the period. Sowell Financial Services LLC acquired a new stake in Novartis AG during the fourth quarter valued at $116,000. The firm owned 10,172 shares of the company's stock after buying an additional 4,493 shares during the period. Bessemer Group Inc. raised its stake in shares of Novartis AG by 10.8% in the fourth quarter. Beacon Financial Group now owns 21,712 shares of the company's stock valued at $1,623,000 after buying an additional 3,526 shares in the last quarter. Moreover, Fernwood Investment Management Llc has 0.1% invested in the company for 30,900 shares.Novartis AG (NYSE NVS) started trading at 83.21 on Early Thur. Novartis AG (ADR) (NYSE:NVS) has risen 7.67% since July 13, 2016 and is uptrending. The relative volume of the stock is 0.79, while its market cap is $217.33 Billion. The firm has a 50-day moving average of $81.82 and a 200-day moving average of $76.18.Novartis AG (NYSE:NVS) last issued its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, April 25th. The company reported $1.13 EPS for the quarter, topping analysts' consensus estimates of $1.10 by $0.03. The business had revenue of $11.54 billion during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $11.59 billion. Novartis AG had a net margin of 13.10% and a return on equity of 15.46%. Novartis AG's revenue was down.5% compared to the same quarter a year ago. During the same quarter a year ago, the company posted $1.17 earnings per share. Equities analysts anticipate that Novartis AG will post $4.72 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. If you are viewing this news story on another site, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of United States & global trademark and copyright laws. The legal version of this article can be accessed at https://www.thecerbatgem.com/2017/07/13/novartis-ag-nysenvs-shares-bought-by-loomis-sayles-co-l-p.html.A number of brokerages have recently issued reports on NVS. Finally, Cowen and Company set a $77.00 target price on Novartis AG and gave the stock a "hold" rating in a research note on Tuesday. Leerink Swann maintained the shares of NVS in report on Thursday, June 22 with "Hold" rating. Finally, Credit Suisse Group downgraded Novartis AG from a "neutral" rating to an "underperform" rating and set a $82.25 target price on the stock.in a report on Wednesday, July 5th. Barclays PLC upgraded shares of Novartis AG from an "underweight" rating to an "equal weight" rating in a research note on Thursday, June 22nd.In related news, major shareholder Bioventures Ltd Novartis purchased 266,667 shares of the company's stock in a transaction dated Wednesday, July 5th. The transaction was disclosed in a document filed with the SEC, which can be accessed through this hyperlink. The stock rose 0.67% or $0.42 reaching $63.31.Zacks reduced stocks of Novartis AG from a "hold" recommendation to a "sell" recommendation in a study on Monday. The Company is engaged in the research, development, manufacturing and marketing of a range of healthcare products led by pharmaceuticals. The Company's divisions include Innovative Medicines, Sandoz, Alcon and Corporate activities.

 




